= V. Discussion <touying:hidden>

== Why Classic Theory Fails for Suspended Films

#text(size: 12pt)[
  Classic models assume a #text(fill: accent)[rigid, infinite plane]. JJS is a #text(fill: accent)[suspended, nm-thick membrane].
]
#v(0.3em)
#grid(
  columns: (1fr, 1fr),
  gutter: 1em,
  [
    #text(size: 11pt)[
      *Rigid plane assumption:*
      - Tip interacts with only a small area
      - No mechanical deformation
      - Force scales as $R$
    ]
    #v(0.3em)
    #text(size: 11pt)[
      *Suspended film reality:*
      - Attractive pressure causes *downward indentation*
      - Effective radius $R_(e f f) >> R_(t i p)$
      - Force scales as $R_(e f f)$ or even $R_(e f f)^2$
    ]
