== PeakForce QNM Dynamic Effects

#text(size: 12pt)[
  The 2 kHz oscillation means each approach is a #text(fill: accent)[dynamic event], not static equilibrium:
]
#v(0.3em)
#grid(
  columns: (1fr, 1fr),
  gutter: 1em,
  [
    #text(size: 12pt)[
      *Viscoelastic overshoot:*
      - Water film relaxation time $tau ~ eta d^3 / gamma$
      - For $d ~ 1$ nm, $tau ~ 10^(-9)$ s
      - Probe transit time $<< tau$ → water cannot equilibrate
      - Apparent force enhanced by dynamic modulus
    ]
    #v(0.3em)
    #text(size: 12pt)[
      *Inertia of film:*
      - 10 nm film has mass $~10^(-15)$ kg per $mu$m²
      - Acceleration $a ~ F / m$ is large
      - Film "sucks" tip in during snap-in
    ]
  ],
  [
    #rect(width: 100%, fill: rgb("#f8f9fa"), radius: 4pt, inset: 8pt)[
      #text(size: 12pt, weight: "bold")[Velocity dependence]
      #v(0.3em)
      #text(size: 11pt)[
        Our data show:
        - 454 nm displacement: $F approx 151$ nN
        - 1500 nm displacement: $F approx 99$ nN
        #v(0.3em)
        Smaller displacement = higher scan speed = stronger snap-in. This is #text(fill: accent)[consistent] with dynamic enhancement.
      ]
    ]
  ]
)

